# Spring Boot Standards

## Context

- Apply when developing Spring Boot applications
- Ensures consistent application structure and configuration
- Promotes maintainable and secure code practices

## Critical Rules

- Use `@SpringBootApplication` annotation only on the main application class
- Externalize all configuration in `application.properties` or `application.yml` files
- Implement global exception handling with `@ControllerAdvice` and `@ExceptionHandler`
- Always use `@Transactional` annotations for methods that modify database state
- Enable and configure Spring Boot Actuator endpoints for monitoring
- Structure packages by feature rather than by layer
- Use constructor injection rather than field injection
- Avoid using `@Autowired` directly on fields

## Examples

<example>
// Good practice - Constructor injection
@Service
public class UserService {
    private final UserRepository userRepository;
    
    public UserService(UserRepository userRepository) {
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
    }
}
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Bad practice - Field injection
@Service
public class UserService {
    @Autowired
    private UserRepository userRepository;
}
</example> 